# regularization is a technique which is used to reduce overfitting in regression models by adding a penalty to the loss function, this reduces the generalization error of the model #nolint
# generalisation error is the measure of how accurately a model is able to predict outcome values for previously unseen data(an estimate of MSE) #nolint
# there are two main types of regularization techniques: ridge regression and lasso regression #nolint
# ridge regression adds a penalty equal to the square of the magnitude of coefficients multiplied by a regularization parameter(lambda) to the loss function #nolint
# lasso regression adds a penalty equal to the absolute value of the magnitude of coefficients multiplied by a regularization parameter(lambda) to the loss function #nolint
# elastic net is a combination of both ridge and lasso regression #nolint
# to do- implement regularization in regression models using R #nolint
